{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8eb95a4a-9ba7-4a15-97a3-a7147b5dc983","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int value) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **MSTest & NUnit** both use `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n- **xUnit** uses a `Skip` property on `[Fact]` or `[Theory]`\n- **TUnit** uses `[Skip(\"reason\")]`\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"339ca559-0946-4f4d-a75f-c56aadcdd3f0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"7C13:2DF061:12E7C5F:1558688:69F9436F"},"id":"017a27ec-60ff-44d1-a218-a42c78a1d686","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.258Z","parentId":"1bd1d411-967e-4aeb-b518-a5693df925e2"}
